Introduction

Kwon Eunbi is a South Korean singer-songwriter, DJ, and actress under Woolim Entertainment.

She debuted as a member of the girl group Ye-A in 2014 before leaving the group shortly after debuting. In 2018, she gained fame by participating in Mnet's Produce 48, finishing 7th and joining the project group IZ*ONE, which debuted in 2018. After the group's disbandment in 2021, she launched her solo career with her debut mini-album 'OPEN'.

Eunbi has also appeared in various variety shows, acted in musicals, and served as a mentor on survival shows. She participated in the 2023 survival show GIRL'S REVERSE and placed 1st, earning her a spot in the group FE:VERSE. She later became a DJ for SBS's radio show Young Street. In 2024, she made her acting debut in the Japanese film series Stolen Identity.
